headline: Chipotle (CMG): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q2 Earnings?
summary: Over the last six months, Chipotle’s shares have sunk to $42.20, producing a disappointing 13.5% loss - a stark contrast to the S&P 500’s 23.2% gain. This was partly driven by its softer quarterly results and may have investors wondering how to approach the situation.
